Flexible box layout in action
In the following example, a container has been set to display: flex, which means that the three child items become flex items The value of justify-content has been set to space-between in order to space the items out evenly on the main axis An equal amount of space is placed between each item with the left and right items being flush with the edges of the flex container You can also see that the items are stretching on the cross axis, due to the default value of align-items being stretch The items stretch to the height of the flex container, making them each appear as tall as the tallest item html<div class="box">
