Aligning content on the cross axis with the align-content property
So far, we have focused on aligning items or individual items inside the area defined by a flex container containing a single line of flex items When flex items are allowed to wrap across multiple lines, the align-content property can be used to control the distribution of space between the lines, also known as packing flex lines For align-content to have an effect, the cross axis dimension (the height in this case) of the flex container must be greater than needed to display the items It then works on all the items as a set The align-content values dictate what happens with the extra available space and the alignment of the entire set of items within it

