The direction of start of the line will also change if you change the flex-direction property â for example, using row-reverse instead of row In this next example, flex-direction: row-reverse and justify-content: flex-end define the direction and location of the items within the flex container In a left to right language, the items line up on the left Try changing flex-direction: row-reverse to flex-direction: row You will see that the items now move to the right-hand side, and the visual order of the items is reversed

