As we have seen from the above examples if our items are allowed to grow and shrink, when there are fewer items in the last row or column then those items grow to fill the available space There are no flexbox features to tell items in one row to line up with items in the row above â each flex line acts like a new flex container It deals with space distribution across the main axis If there is only one item, and that item is allowed to grow, it will fill the axis just as if you had a single item flex container If you want layout in two dimensions then you probably want grid layout This example demonstrates the difference, using CSS grid layout to create a layout with as many columns of at least 160px as will fit, distributing the extra space between all columns

