This is the difference between one and two-dimensional layouts In a one-dimensional layout method like flexbox, we only control the row or column In a two-dimensional grid layout, we control both at the same time If you want the space distribution row by row, use Flexbox If you don't, use CSS grid How do flexbox-based grid systems work Flexbox-based layouts can be forced to line up as grid systems, but that is not the intended purpose of flexbox If you assign percentage widths to flex items â either using flex-basis or by adding a width to the item itself and leaving the value of flex-basis as auto â you can give the impression of a two-dimensional layout In this example, flex-grow and flex-shrink have been set to 0 to make inflexible flex items The flexibility is controlled via percentages

